ce:section.ce:para:
The hydrochars obtained from the aforementioned HTC process were also further carbonized. For that purpose, approximately 1 g of hydrochar was placed in a previously weighed ceramic boat and introduced into a tubular furnace. The latter was continuously flushed by nitrogen flowing at 90 mL/min, and heated at 2 °C/min to 900 °C. This final temperature was maintained for 1 h before cooling to room temperature under N2 flow. This procedure prevented any oxidation of the sample. The latter was then stored in a desiccator and weighed. The carbonization yield (Y

                              C
                           ) was calculated as the mass ratio of carbon material to hydrochar on a dry basis. The total carbon yield (Y

                              T
                           ) was also calculated as the mass ratio of the final carbon material to the raw flax powder or fiber, again on a dry basis.
